    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes, we should apply these to ``other`` alignment. ``cond`` is a boolean array, virtually always the dim same shape as the calling frame, if it is not (or a scalar), then I would say simply raise. \r\n\r\nalternatively, we could add additional keyword ``broadcast_axis`` to apply to the cond (which passes thru to ``.align``), but this is quickly getting complicated."
